\id GAL - Akawaio New Testament Translation Project 
\h KARE'SIYA 
\toc1 Kareta Paarʉ Nennoko'pʉ Kare'siya Pon Kon Ena' 
\toc2 Kare'siysa 
\toc3 Kare'siysa 
\mt2 Kareta Paarʉ Nennoko'pʉ 
\mt1 Kare'siya Pon Kon 
\mt2 Ena' 
\imt1 Ekamanin 
\ip Wakʉ itekare Sises pɨ' epiya'tɨ tekamasen pe mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tereutanʉ'sen pe koro'tau Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen ka'pon amʉ' koro'tau, usekama'popɨ' nɨto' e'seporo'pʉ man Mosi' winon pe' awɨrɨ ka'pon e'to' pe iyesi, i'nai rɨ Kʉri'san pe e'nɨto' pe tukai'. Paarʉ uya to' eseru'ka'pʉ mɨrɨ i'se e'nɨto' pe pʉra serɨ esi tukai'—mɨrɨ kuru nin, Kʉrai yau uko'man nɨto' esi apurɨto' rɨken iwinɨ na'ne' tanporon kon ekonekato' Papa pokon pe. E'tane Kare'siya so'sii amʉ' koro'tau, Roman nono, Eisa Mʉre'pʉ yau, ka'pon amʉ' uye'sa' esi'pʉ, mɨrɨpan kon uya Paarʉ ewa'noma'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' uya ta'pʉ ka'pon uya kuru rɨ marɨ apurɨto' pe iyesi tekonekato' pe Papa ya' Main, Mosi' winon nʉnonka'pʉ. 
\ip \bk Kareta Paarʉ Nennoko'pʉ Kare'siya Pon Kon Ena'\bk* e'menuka'pʉ kamoro itano'masa' kon serɨ ennakanin enupan nɨto' ke, na'ponin pe i'nai rɨ te'sen apurɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iku'to' ya'. Paarʉ epiya'tɨ itekare ekamai' Sises nennoko'pʉ pe tesa'to' wa'kʉtʉ pe. Ta iya, ikɨ'masa' itekare ekamai' enno'sa' pe iye'to' pe esi, Papa winon pe, ka'pon meruntɨrʉ winɨ pen, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ enno'sa' pe iyesi'pʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen piya' kuru. Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ si te'sei'pɨ'to' to' eseru'ka pe emo'ka'pʉ iya apurɨto' winɨ rɨken nɨ ka'pon amʉ' ekoneka Papa pokon pe. Iu'matʉ airo'nan isa'ta yau, Paarʉ uya enpoikasa' Kʉri'san amʉ' nʉkupʉnʉ e'kupʉ tiwano' ti'naino pe rɨ tʉusi'nʉnkato' winɨ Kʉrai apurɨto' moron nʉ'pʉ pe. 
\iot Iyawon Ekamanin 
\io1 Ekamanin (1:1-10) 
\io1 Paarʉ meruntɨrʉ itekare ekamai' enno'sa' pe (1:11—2:21) 
\io1 Papa uya eke wakʉ nonkasa' ekareei (3:1—4:31) 
\io1 Ɨnʉ' enawon kon pen nɨ Kʉri'san amʉ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ to' tʉrawasooi (5:1—6:10) 
\io1 Iu'matʉ (6:11-18) 
\c 1  
\s1 Miyarɨ Ta Paarʉ Uya 
\p  
\v 1 Paarʉ, enno'sa' itekare ekamai'—ka'pon amʉ' winɨpai enno'sa' pen, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ka'pon nennoko'pʉ pen, e'tane Sises Kʉrai mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa, Ikʉipʉnʉ, i'mʉ'sa'kanin nʉ'pʉ iyerikʉ'pʉ apai nennoko'pʉ winɨpaino—  
\v 2 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tanporon kon tonpa ton upiyawon kon winɨpaino, 
\p So'si ton Kare'siya po'nan enakan: 
\p  
\v 3 Tɨwɨ wakʉ nonkasa' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉusewankamai' pʉra ɨwe'to' kon Papa, ukʉipʉnʉ kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Itepuru Sises Kʉrai winɨpaino nesii ɨyenakan kon pe.  
\v 4 Kʉrɨ rɨ Sises Kʉrai iye'tʉsa' rʉ'pʉ umakooi kon iwano' pe umo'kanin kon pe serɨ pe na'ne' ɨri pe e'nɨto' apai, urɨ'nokon e'to' itese' pɨ' Papa, ukʉipʉnʉ kon e'to' i'se awɨrɨ, nesii ɨyenakan kon pe.  
\v 5 Kʉrɨ rɨ Papa iwano' pe eke pe iku'to' nesii tɨwɨrɨ rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tɨwɨrɨ rɨ. Amen. 
\s1 Tʉron Nɨ Itekare Pen 
\p  
\v 6 Usewansiukasa' man inke pʉra kuru rɨ ɨkɨ'manin nʉ'pʉ kon wakʉ nonkasa' Kʉrai uya winɨ nonka auya'nokon pɨ',\f + \fr 1:6 \fq eke wakʉ Kʉrai nʉnonka'pʉ; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq eke wakʉ innonka'pʉ\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨyera'tɨ kon tʉponaron nɨ itekare winɨkʉi'—  
\v 7 itekare parɨ pen kuru rɨ winɨkʉi'. Tʉron kon ka'pon amʉ' uya ɨyeno'ma kon poken iyesi utaipon nɨto' ya', mɨrɨpan kon esi wakʉ Kʉrai ekareei wʉuka i'se.  
\v 8 E'tane pʉra rɨ, ina mɨrɨ pe pʉra inserʉ Epʉn poino uya rɨ tʉron nɨ itekare ekama pe iyesi yau, serɨ ina nekamayai'ne' ɨpɨ'nokon warai pen nɨ, tɨwɨ ipa'nʉ'sa' pe nesii!  
\v 9 Ina uya taka'sa' na'ne' kasa rɨ, takapʉ uya kanan serɨ pe: Ɨnʉ' uya tʉron nɨ itekare ekama pe iyesi yau ɨpɨ'nokon, ananʉmʉ'pʉ kon waraino pen, tɨwɨ ipa'nʉ'sa' pe nesii! 
\p  
\v 10 Ka'pon amʉ' uya pe' uyapurɨto' i'se esi serɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra Papa uya katɨ? Mɨrɨ pe pʉra ka'pon amʉ' katɨ ɨnpori'mapai esi? Ka'pon amʉ' ɨnpori'mapai esi yau, Kʉrai poitorʉ pe pʉra rɨ esi mɨrɨ. 
\s1 Papa Uya Paarʉ Kɨ'ma'pʉ 
\p  
\v 11 I'tu auya'nokon i'se e'ai', utonpa ton, sekamayai'ne' wakʉ itekare esi ka'pon nʉkoneka'pʉ pen.  
\v 12 Ka'pon winɨ uneporo'pʉ pen nɨ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra uyenupasa' rʉ'pʉ ipɨ' pen nɨ; e'tane ru'ku, Sises Kʉrai uya enpoika winɨ uneporo'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 13 Apʉne pʉra eta'pʉ auya'nokon uko'mamʉ'pʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' eseru yau, ɨsɨ pe rɨ Papa so'sii kota'ma'pʉ uya, anma'tanʉ'pai rɨ esi'pʉ.\x - \xo 1:13 \xt Inkupʉ'pʉ 8:3; 22:4-5; 26:9-11\x* 
\v 14 Esuwerʉ amʉ' eseru yau ukɨɨyisi kaisaron kon entai rɨ utɨsa' esi'pʉ utamokori ton eseru kuru awɨrɨ e'nɨ pɨ'.\x - \xo 1:14 \xt Inkupʉ'pʉ 22:3\x* 
\v 15 E'tane Papa, uyamanin nʉ'pʉ entu'pʉ si'kɨrɨ\f + \fr 1:15 \fq entu'pʉ si'kɨrɨ; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq usan ewan apai\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ukɨ'ma'pʉ iya wakʉ nonkasa' tʉuya winɨ, esi'pʉ pori' pe  
\v 16 tʉmu ɨnenpoikapai uyau itekareei ekamanin pe e'to' pe Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen koro'tau. Mɨrɨ a'tai, ɨnʉ' rɨ ekama'po'pʉ uya pen upika'tɨto' pe iya,\x - \xo 1:16 \xt Inkupʉ'pʉ 9:3-6; 22:6-10; 26:13-18\x* 
\v 17 utɨsa' pʉra rɨ iyesi Surusiran pona urawɨron kon itekare ekamai' enno'sa' kon ense'na, e'tane ru'ku utɨ'pʉ inke pʉra Arepiya pona, emennʉ'pʉ tenna'po ton pe Tamaskas pona. 
\p  
\v 18 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ osorʉwau wʉipiya tʉpo, utɨ'pʉ Surusiran pona Pi'ta\f + \fr 1:18 \fq Pi'ta; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Ke'pas \ft - Kiri' maimu yau\f* enupankase'na, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ipiyau uko'mamʉ'pʉ 15 kaisa rɨ wʉi.\x - \xo 1:18 \xt Inkupʉ'pʉ 9:26-30\x* 
\v 19 Tʉron kon itekare ekamai' enno'sa' kon ensa' uya pʉra iyesi—Isens rɨken, Itepuru akon.  
\v 20 I'nai rɨ kuru ekama uya, Papa uya entane, serɨ simenukayai'ne' esi kasi pe pen.  
\v 21 Mɨrɨ tʉpo utɨ'pʉ Siriya itese' pata pona mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Siri'siya itese' pata pona.  
\v 22 Ka'pon pe urɨ i'tu so'si amʉ' Kʉrai yau te'san Isutiya pon kon uya pʉra iyesi'pʉ.  
\v 23 Uyekareei rɨken eta'pʉ to' uya, “Ka'pon, ɨsɨ pe so'si kota'manin nʉ'pʉ man tapurɨsen ima'tanʉkʉ i'se te'sa' rʉ'pʉ ekareei ekama pɨ',” tawon.  
\v 24 Mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Papa apurɨpɨtʉ'pʉ to' uya urɨ uriya'. 
\c 2  
\s1 Paarʉ Anʉmʉ'pʉ Itekare Ekamai' Enno'sa' Kon Uya 
\p  
\v 1 14 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya tʉpo, Surusiran pona kanan utɨ'pʉ Panapas pokon pe. Serɨ a'tai, Tai'tas nɨrɨ arɨ'pʉ uya uya'kɨrɨ.  
\v 2 Isenpoikasa' rʉ'pʉ maimu eikʉ pe utɨ'pʉ itekare ekamai' to' pɨ' mɨrɨ unekamanʉ Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen koro'tau. E'tane serɨ kupʉ'pʉ uya ama'ai, kamoro itepuru pe to' esi tato' ton iwano' pe, apʉne pʉra enari'ke' pe esi pɨ' eka'tumʉ, mɨrɨ pe pʉra eka'tunsa' esi iwotori'pɨ pʉra na'kɨ ko, tukai'.  
\v 3 E'tane rɨ Tai'tas, uya'kɨrɨ iye'sa' rʉ'pʉ a'kwarʉka'pʉ pen nɨ tʉyun pi'pɨ puturʉkato' pe iya, Kiri' pe rɨ iye'tane.  
\v 4 Serɨ eseru usenpoika'pʉ, apʉne pʉra ennakanin nan tonpa ton uyee'pʉ ina uya i'tu pʉra ɨ'rɨ kan to' uyee'pʉ tukai', e'tane to' kenʉ' uyee'pʉ ina nʉkupʉnʉ mɨrɨ pe pʉra ina uko'mamʉ eseru ense'na, Kʉrai Sises nʉmo'ka'san pe esii'ma, ina kanan ku'se'na a'sisa' kon pe.  
\v 5 Mara rʉ'kwɨ rɨ to' weyu ke to' repa'pʉ ina uya pen, mɨrɨ yau i'nairon wakʉ itekare uko'manto' pe ɨpiyau'nokon. 
\p  
\v 6 Kamoro eke pe na'ne' nan—ɨ'rɨ pe rɨ to' esi'pʉ uya tʉron nɨ pe rɨ to' kupʉ pʉra iyesi urɨ pona; Papa uya kɨpo'pon winɨ rɨ eseru wannɨ aimenka pʉra iyesi—kamoro ka'pon amʉ' uya ɨ'rɨ ke rɨ uyekareei ponantɨsa' pʉra iyesi.\x - \xo 2:6 \xt Isu'taronomi 10:17\x* 
\v 7 Tʉron nɨ pe, to' uya ene'pʉ urepasa' itekare ekamato' tʉrawasooi ke Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen\f + \fr 2:7 \fq Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq tʉyun kon pi'pɨ puturʉka'pʉ kon pen\f* pana ya', Esuwerʉ amʉ'\f + \fr 2:7 \fq Esuwerʉ amʉ'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq tʉyun kon pi'pɨ puturʉka'pʉ kon; \ft v. 8-9 nɨrɨ.\f* pɨ' Pi'ta uya itekare ekamato' pe irepa'pʉ itʉrawasooi ke na'ne' kasa.  
\v 8 Apʉne pʉra Papa, Pi'ta e'tʉrawasomato' yau tʉrawaso pe iye'sa' Esuwerʉ amʉ' pɨ' itekare ekamai' enno'sa' tʉrawasooi yau nɨrɨ e'tʉrawasoma'pʉ, mɨrɨpan nɨ marɨ esi'pʉ utʉrawasooi yau itekare ekamai' enno'sa' pe Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen pana ya'.  
\v 9 Isens, Pi'ta\f + \fr 2:9 \fq Pi'ta, \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra \fq Ke'pas \ft Kiri' maimu yau; v. 11, 14 nɨrɨ.\f* mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Isaan, anʉnsan kon itepuru ton pe uya urɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Panapas a'si'pʉ temiyatʉ kon enwo'netʉ ke tʉtonpa kon pe, wakʉ nonkasa' uyena' to'ka'nʉkʉ tʉuya'nokon a'tai. To' uya ewai' ta'pʉ, ina utɨto' pe iyesi a'tai Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen ton piya', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kamoro Esuwerʉ amʉ' piya'.  
\v 10 To' uya rɨken ekama'po'pʉ miyarɨ rɨ entu'manin nan tʉku'se ina e'to' pe tenu kon yau, serɨ kuru rɨ esi'pʉ ɨnku'pai e'pɨ'to'. 
\s1 Paarʉ Uya Pi'ta Pɨrɨ'ka'pʉ 
\p  
\v 11 Pi'ta uye'sa' a'tai Antiyo' pona, ipɨrɨ'ka'pʉ uya itenpa tau, apʉne pʉra ipoken pʉra kuru rɨ iye'sa' pɨ'.  
\v 12 Isens piyapai ka'pon amʉ' uyepʉ wapiya, Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen pokon pe tenta'napɨ'sen pe iyesi'pʉ. E'tane to' uye'sa' a'tai, to' piyapai itama'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iye'wʉrʉuka'pʉ, apʉne pʉra enari'kena' pe tesi wenai, iputurʉka tawon nan tonpa pe te'san pɨ'.  
\v 13 Tʉron kon Esuwerʉ amʉ' e'sara'tɨ'pʉ wakʉ pe iye'ku'to' eseru yau, mɨrɨ pɨ', wakʉ pe to' e'ku'to' winɨ Panapas rɨ nɨrɨ utano'ma'pʉ. 
\p  
\v 14 I'nairon itekare poro pʉra to' esi ensa' uya a'tai, tu'kan kon koro'tau Pi'ta pɨ' ta'pʉ uya, “Esuwerʉ pon pe ɨwesi, e'tane rɨ Esuwerʉ pon pen kasa ɨuko'mamʉ, Esuwerʉ pon kasa pʉra. Ɨ'rɨ kasa ken si Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen a'kwarʉka auya Esuwerʉ amʉ' eseru yau to' utɨto' pe? 
\p  
\v 15 “Urɨ'nokon kamoro tentu'pʉ kon winɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ', ‘Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen tʉmakooikena' nan’ pen.  
\v 16 E'tane urɨ'nokon uya i'tu Papa uya kamo Sises Kʉrai apurɨto' esanon nɨken anʉmʉ. Mɨrɨ kasa iyesi wenai, urɨ'nokon uya nɨrɨ Kʉrai Sises apurɨto' esi apurɨto' poro wakʉ pe ekonekan nɨto' pe, main awɨrɨ e'nɨ winɨ pen, apʉne pʉra main awɨrɨ te'se ɨnʉ' rɨ ekoneka pʉra iyesi wakʉ pe.\x - \xo 2:16 \xt Eren 143:2; Ron 3:20-22\x* 
\p  
\v 17 “Kʉrai yau wakʉ pe ekonekan nɨto' warinpa koro'tau iyesi yau, tʉmakooi ke si usi'tun nɨto' ya' enan, makoi rɨ tʉrawasoma Kʉrai uya, ta iya pe' e'kwa pe iyesi mɨ? Kane ku!  
\v 18 Unma'tanʉkʉ'pʉ amɨ uya pe kanan iyesi a'tai, main i'kwɨ'nin pe esi tukai' usenpoika.  
\v 19 Main poro, eri'sa' main pona, uko'manto' pe Papa iwano' pe.  
\v 20 Urɨ e'pokapɨ'sa' kurusu' pona Kʉrai a'kɨrɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uko'mamʉ pʉra iyesi, e'tane Kʉrai uko'mamʉ uyau. Uko'manto' uko'manyai'ne' ipun yau, Papa Mumu apurɨto' uya yau uko'mamʉ, ui'nʉnkanin nʉ'pʉ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉmɨrɨ pe iye'tʉsa' rʉ'pʉ uiwano' pe.  
\v 21 Wakʉ nonkasa' Papa uya nonka uya pen, Main poro ipoken e'nɨto' eporo pe iyesi yau, Kʉrai uma'ta'pʉ pe iyesi notʉn pe rɨ!”\f + \fr 2:21 \ft Tʉron kon enpoikanin nan uya main nʉ'pʉ i'ma'ka v.14 airɨ.\f* 
\c 3  
\s1 Apurɨto' Mɨrɨ Pe Pʉra Main, Mosi' Winon Awɨrɨ E'nɨto' 
\p  
\v 1 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon pu'pʉnon Kare'siya pon kon! Ɨnʉ' uya ayawopasa' kon? Ɨyenu kon yau kuru Sises usene'pʉ kɨpo'po kurusu' pona ipokapɨ'sa' pe.  
\v 2 Tikin nan ɨni'tupai e'ai' ɨwinɨ'nokon: Main, Mosi' winon pe' awɨrɨ ɨwesi kon pɨ' Papa A'kwarʉ eporo'pʉ auya'nokon, ɨneta'pʉ kon katɨ apurɨ auya'nokon pɨ'?  
\v 3 Pu'pʉra kuru rɨ pe' ɨwesi kon? Papa A'kwarʉ a'kɨrɨ ɨye'sara'tɨ kon tʉpo, serɨ pe i'se ɨwe'to' kon pe' eporo i'se ɨwesi kon ka'pon nʉkupʉnʉ winɨ?  
\v 4 Ɨ'rɨto' pe pʉra rɨ pe' ɨyekota'masa' kon? Ɨ'rɨ ku'nin pe rɨ iyesi'pʉ mɨrɨ.  
\v 5 Main, Mosi' winon pe' awɨrɨ ɨwesi kon pɨ' Papa uya Ta'kwarʉ ke ɨrepa'pʉ kon, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ eke tʉtʉrawasooi pe' kupʉ'pʉ iya ɨ'koro'tau'nokon, mɨrɨ pe pʉra ɨneta'pʉ kon katɨ apurɨ auya'nokon pɨ'? 
\p  
\v 6 Epʉra'an i'tutɨ': “Papa apurɨ'pʉ iya, mɨrɨpan i'tu'pʉ iya wakʉ ipokena' e' pe kuru.”\f + \fr 3:6 \ft Iseneses 15:6\f*\x - \xo 3:6 \xt Ron 4:3\x* 
\v 7 Ito'ka'nʉ'tɨ', kamoro apurɨnin nan esi Epʉra'an munkɨ amʉ' pe tukai'.\x - \xo 3:7 \xt Ron 4:16\x* 
\v 8 Itekare e'menukasa' uya pena rɨ ensa' esi'pʉ, Papa uya Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen konekato' oton apurɨto' to' uya winɨ, mɨrɨ uya iye'kupʉ rawɨrɨ rɨ itekare ekama'pʉ Epʉra'an pɨ': “Tanporon kon tʉpataron kon pʉremato' uya oton ɨporo,”\f + \fr 3:8 \ft Iseneses 12:3; 18:18; 22:18\f* tukai'.  
\v 9 Mɨrɨpan kamoro apurɨto' esanon pʉremasa' Epʉra'an, apurɨto' esa' pokon pe. 
\p  
\v 10 Tanporo kamoro Main pɨ' tʉuta'sii' te'san esi pa'nʉ'nɨsa' o'no, apʉne pʉra iye'menukasa': “Ipa'nʉ'sa' kon pe kamoro esi tanporo Main apon pɨ' iye'menukasa' kupʉ pɨ' te'san pen,”\f + \fr 3:10 \ft Isu'taronomi 27:26 (LXX)\f* tukai'.  
\v 11 Ene rɨ, ɨnʉ' rɨ koneka Main uya pʉra iyesi Papa enu yau, apʉne pʉra, “Ipokena' pe te'sen uko'mamʉ apurɨto' winɨ,”\f + \fr 3:11 \ft Apa'ka' 2:4\f* tasa' iya.  
\v 12 Main esi apurɨto' pokon pen; mɨrɨ e'tane, “Kʉrɨ rɨ serɨ ton ku'nin uko'mamʉ rɨ mɨrɨ winɨ,”\f + \fr 3:12 \ft Ripaiti'kas 18:5\f* tasa'.  
\v 13 Kʉrai uya uye'masa' kon, main uya pa'nʉ'nɨsa' apai, ipa'nʉ'sa' pe urɨ'nokon pe tenai', apʉne pʉra iye'menukasa', “Ipa'nʉ'sa' kon kamoro yʉi pɨ' isinkasa' kon,”\f + \fr 3:13 \ft Isu'taronomi 21:23\f* tukai'.  
\v 14 Uye'masa' iya 'nokon, Epʉra'an pʉremasa' rʉ'pʉ utɨto' pe Esuwerʉ amʉ' pen pona Kʉrai Sises poro, mɨrɨpan apurɨto' winɨ Ita'kwarʉ usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ ipɨ' epoto' pe. 
\s1 Main Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Usauro'nɨsa' Rʉ'pʉ 
\p  
\v 15 Utonpa ton, apʉne wʉi kaisa rɨ uko'man nɨto' eseru pɨ' sekamai'ya. Ɨnʉ' uya rɨ ka'pon amʉ' ekonekasa' rʉ'pʉ pena iteseru ye' awɨrɨ isara'tɨsa' mo'ka mɨrɨ pe pʉra itonpa'tɨ pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ. Mɨrɨ na'ne' kasa serɨ esi mɨrɨ.  
\v 16 Usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ ton usekama'pʉ Epʉra'an pana ya' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ imu ena'. Itekare iye'menukasa' uya, “ɨmunkɨ amʉ',” tasa' pʉra iyesi, tu'kan kon ta e'kwa pe, e'tane, “ɨmʉre,”\f + \fr 3:16 \ft Iseneses 12:7; 13:15; 24:7\f* tasa' iya, tikin nan pɨ'; kʉrɨ rɨ si esi Kʉrai.  
\v 17 Se kasa ta uya e'kwa pe iyesi: Main, 430 kaisa rɨ wʉipiya tʉpo isekamasa' rʉ'pʉ uya Papa ekoneka'pʉ ka'pon amʉ' pokon pe iye'sara'tɨsa' rʉ'pʉ kuka pʉra iyesi, ikupʉ tukai' usauro'nɨ'pʉ eno'manin pe.\x - \xo 3:17 \xt E'sotas 12:40\x* 
\v 18 Apʉne pʉra Papa uya repan nɨto' esi yau main awɨrɨ e'nɨsa' wenai, isauro'sa' rʉ'pʉ wenai iyesi pen nɨ mɨrɨ, e'tane Papa uya, wakʉ nonkasa' tʉuya yau, Epʉra'an repa'pʉ iya ike tʉusauro'sa' poro.\x - \xo 3:18 \xt Ron 4:14\x* 
\p  
\v 19 Ɨ'rɨ ken si ku'nin pe main esi mɨrɨ? Iponantɨsa' mɨrɨ makoi esi pɨ', ekamasa' rʉ'pʉ Epʉra'an pa rʉ'pʉ uyepʉ pona rɨ. Papa uya main tʉrʉ'pʉ inserʉ amʉ' poro Mosi', ka'sanawon wannɨ ena' ka'pon amʉ' enakan pe.  
\v 20 Tikin nan nɨken Papa,\f + \fr 3:20 \fq Tikin nan nɨken Papa; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Papa esi tikin sarɨ esii'ma iku'nin\f* mɨrɨpan main uye'sa' pʉra iyesi iwinɨpai kuru. 
\p  
\v 21 Main ken pe' si esi Papa usauro'sa' ewa'nomanin pe? Kane! Main e'tʉsa' pe iyesi yau uko'man nɨto' ne'nin pe, ipokena' pe e'nɨto' ne'seporoi'no main winɨ.  
\v 22 E'tane iye'menukasa' itekare uya ekama tanporo orʉ esi makoi na'si'pʉ pe, mɨrɨ si usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ ipɨ', iye'tʉsa' rʉ'pʉ pe te'sen apurɨto' poro Sises Kʉrai yau, e'tʉto' pe kamoro apurɨnin nan ena'. 
\p  
\v 23 Serɨ apurɨto' uyepʉ rawɨrɨ, Main uya a'sin nɨsa' esi'pʉ, a'kon nɨsa' iya esi'pʉ, apurɨto' usenpoika pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ.  
\v 24 Mɨrɨ yau Main e'tʉsa' esi'pʉ esa' wannɨ pe uyanin kon pe Kʉrai piya',\f + \fr 3:24 \fq uyanin kon pe Kʉrai piya'; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Kʉrai uyepʉ pʉ'kʉ pona rɨ.\f* ekonekan nɨto' pe apurɨto' winɨ.  
\v 25 Apurɨto' si uye'sa' pɨ', main o'no pʉra e'nɨ'nokon serɨ. 
\s1 Papa Munkɨ Amʉ' 
\p  
\v 26 Tanporo Papa munkɨ amʉ' pe ɨwesi kon Kʉrai Sises apurɨto' auya'nokon poro,  
\v 27 apʉne pʉra tanporo ɨmɨrɨ'nokon ipokon pe iyenasa' kon ɨyepa'taisima kon yau Kʉrai ya' epontɨsa' mɨrɨ Kʉrai ke.  
\v 28 Mɨrɨ yau Esuwerʉ pʉra rɨ iyesi, Esuwerʉ pen pʉra rɨ, poitorʉ pʉra rɨ, a'sisa' pen pʉra rɨ, warawo' pʉra rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ uri'san pʉra iyesi, apʉne pʉra tikin nɨ ɨwesi kon Kʉrai Sises yau.  
\v 29 Kʉrai iwano' pe ɨwesi kon yau, Epʉra'an payan ton pe ɨwesi kon mɨrɨ, mɨrɨ yau usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ epoton kon pe.\x - \xo 3:29 \xt Ron 4:13\x* 
\c 4  
\p  
\v 1 Se ta uya, inonkasa' rʉ'pʉ anʉnnin esi pɨ' mʉre pe rɨ marɨ, poitorʉ kasa pʉra tʉpona rɨ iyesi pen nɨ, tanporon nɨ tiwano' esa' pe rɨ te'tane.  
\v 2 Terasu ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tesan non nɨ enau iyesi ikʉipʉnʉ nʉkuu'pʉ iweyu e'seporo pona rɨ.  
\v 3 Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ marɨ, mʉre amʉ' pe e'nɨ a'tai, apiyo' pe e'nɨ'pʉ orʉ eseru o'noro.  
\v 4 E'tane si iweyu kuru e'seposa' a'tai, Papa uya Tʉmu ennoko'pʉ, uri'san yai iyentu'pʉ, main o'no iyentu'pʉ,  
\v 5 kamoro main o'no te'san e'manin pe, imunkɨ amʉ' pe kuru e'nɨto' epoto' pe.  
\v 6 Apʉne pʉra imunkɨ pe ɨwesi kon pɨ', Papa uya Tʉmu A'kwarʉ ennoko'pʉ uyewan kon ya', Ita'kwarʉ tʉukɨ'pɨ'nʉnsen, “Apa,\f + \fr 4:6 \fq Apa; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq Papai \ft Arami' maimu yau.\f* Papai,” tukai'.  
\v 7 Mɨrɨ wenai poitorʉ pe ɨwesi kon pen, e'tane imu pe; imu pe si ɨwesi kon pɨ', Papa uya ɨkonekasa' kon tʉnnonka'pʉ anʉnnin pe.\x - \xo 4:7 \xt Ron 8:15-17\x* 
\s1 Paarʉ Usewankama Kare'siya Pon Kon Pɨ' 
\p  
\v 8 Pena rɨ, Papa i'tu auya'nokon pʉra iyesi a'tai, apiyo' pe ɨwesi'pʉ kon kamo ti'naino kon papa amʉ' pen iwano' pe.  
\v 9 E'tane nin si serɨ si Papa i'tu auya'nokon—mɨrɨ pe pʉra ru'ku, Papa uya ɨi'tu kon—nai pe ken si ɨyenna'po kon mɨ ton ɨ'sɨ'mʉnon, ɨri ton eseru ya'? To' uya rɨ pe' aya'sikapʉ kon kanan i'se ɨwesi kon?  
\v 10 Eke ton pe te'sen ton wʉi amʉ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ kapʉi amʉ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ pata weyu ton mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ wʉipiya ton kupʉ auya'nokon!  
\v 11 Uyewankamayatʉi', ɨpɨ'nokon nɨ sa'ne wakʉ rɨ ku'to' uya i'ma'kasa' uya pɨ'. 
\p  
\v 12 Ɨyekama'po uya 'nokon kuru, utonpa ton, urɨ kasa enatɨ', akasa'nokon enasa' pɨ'. Ɨri pe uku'sa' auya'nokon pʉra rɨ man.  
\v 13 Mi'tuyatʉi'ne' kasa rɨ, apʉne pʉra takuru'ke esi pɨ' ɨmɨrɨ'nokon pɨ' kuru wapiya wakʉ itekare ekama'pʉ uya.  
\v 14 Takuru'ke rɨ e'to' e'tane ɨi'tupɨ'to' kon pe, ɨri pe rɨ ukuu'pʉ auya'nokon pen mɨrɨ pe pʉra upɨ' rɨ ɨunuirata'pʉ kon pen nɨ. E'tane ru'ku, uyereutanʉkʉ'pʉ auya'nokon Papa inserʉʉi pe esi kasa rɨ, Kʉrai Sises pe esi kasa rɨ.  
\v 15 Ɨ'rɨ pe tanporo rɨ pori' pe ɨwe'to' kon enasa' nai? Mɨrɨ rɨ ekama uya, mɨrɨ ku'sa' auya'nokon pe iyesi yau, ɨyenu kon nɨ mʉmo'katʉi'no uyena' itʉrʉ kon pa.  
\v 16 Ɨyeyaton kon pe pe' enasa' serɨ i'nairon tekamai' ɨpɨ'nokon? 
\p  
\v 17 Kamoro esi ɨmo'kapai'nokon kuru rɨ tʉwinɨkʉi'no kon, e'tane wakʉto' pe pʉra rɨ. Ina piyapai rɨ nin ene amʉ' pe ɨku'pai'nokon to' esi, ɨwesi kon pa to' winɨkʉi'no kon pe kuru.  
\v 18 Wakʉ pe rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ kuru ɨnku'pai ɨwesi kon a'tai, wakʉ iwano' pe iyesi pɨ', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ mɨrɨ kasa te'sen pe tɨwɨrɨ rɨ, ɨpiyau'nokon nɨken esi a'tai pen.  
\v 19 Umunkɨ amʉ' rʉ'kwɨ, itiwano' pe e'tinkaka'sa' kanan na'ne' nan, Kʉrai e'kapʉ ayau'nokon pʉ'kʉ pona,  
\v 20 ɨpiyau'nokon kuru e'pai e'ai' serɨ pe umaimu ensima pe, apʉne pʉra ɨpɨ'nokon usewankama pɨ'! 
\s1 Ekarʉ Mɨrɨ Awonsi'kɨ Sera 
\p  
\v 21 Apʉne upana'tɨtɨ', ɨmɨrɨ'nokon main o'no e'paino kon, i'tu auya'nokon pʉra pe' nai main uya rɨ tasa'?  
\v 22 Apʉne pʉra iye'menukasa' esi, Epʉra'an esi'pʉ asa'ron kon imu, tikin nan esi'pʉ poitorʉ pe te'sen uri'san winɨpaino, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ tʉron nɨ ɨnʉ' apiyo' pen nɨ uri'san winɨpaino.\x - \xo 4:22 \xt Iseneses 16:15; 21:2\x* 
\v 23 Imu poitorʉ pe te'sen uri'san winɨpaino esi'pʉ entun eseru yau rɨ iyentusa' pe; e'tane imu apiyo' pen uri'san winɨ iyentusa' esi'pʉ iye'kupʉ tukai' usauro'nɨsa' otori'pɨ pe. 
\p  
\v 24 Serɨ ton amʉ' anʉmʉ pe iyesi i'tuto' ipɨ' pe, apʉne pʉra pʉsamoro uri'sami'si amʉ' esi asa'ron ekonekan nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ pe. Tikin nan ekonekan nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ esi Sainai Wʉpʉ winon, apiyo' ton pe tʉumu'tasen: Pʉse rɨ pʉse rɨ Ekarʉ.  
\v 25 Ekarʉ si esi Sainai Wʉpʉ, Arepiya pon pe rɨ mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ serɨ pe na'ne' eke pata Surusiran kaisa rɨ iyesi, apʉne pʉra tʉmunkɨ amʉ' pokon pe apiyo' pe iyesi pɨ'.\f + \fr 4:25 \fq iyesi \ft ta pɨ' na'ne' esi Ekarʉ pɨ' mɨrɨ pe pʉra eke pata Surusiran pɨ' rɨ.\f* 
\v 26 E'tane Surusiran ka'tau na'ne' esi ɨnʉ' apiyo' pe pʉra rɨ, kʉrɨ rɨ si kʉrɨ rɨ usan kon.  
\v 27 Apʉne pʉra iye'menukasa': 
\q1 “Epori'makɨ tʉumu'tasen ye' pen uri'san, 
\q2 mʉre amʉ' entunʉ'nin pen; 
\q1 eke pe ɨkɨ'pɨ'nʉnkɨ, 
\q2 ɨmɨrɨ entun nɨto' pe e'tinkan nɨsa' i'tunin pen; 
\q1 apʉne pʉra tu'ke imunkɨ inonkasa' uri'san esi pɨ' 
\q2 tʉtaan'pʉ kenan entai,”\f + \fr 4:27 \ft Aisaya 54:1\f* 
\m tukai'. 
\p  
\v 28 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon si, utonpa ton, esi Aisi' kasa, usauro'nɨsa' rʉ'pʉ iye'kupʉ tukai' munkɨ pe.  
\v 29 Mɨrɨ a'tai, imu, entun eseru yau rɨ iyentusa' rʉ'pʉ uya Iya'kwarʉ winɨ iyentusa' kota'ma'pʉ. Mɨrɨ kasa rɨ si iyesi serɨ pe.\x - \xo 4:29 \xt Iseneses 21:9\x* 
\v 30 E'tane ɨ'rɨ ken nɨkayan imenukasa' itekare? “Uri'san poitorʉ pe te'sen mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ imʉre inonkakɨ, apʉne pʉra poitorʉ pe te'sen mʉre uya ɨnʉ' enawon pen mʉre pokon pe inonkasa' rʉ'pʉ anʉmʉ pen mɨrɨ,”\f + \fr 4:30 \ft Iseneses 21:10\f* tawon.  
\v 31 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', utonpa ton, urɨ'nokon esi poitorʉ uri'san munkɨ pe pʉra, e'tane ɨnʉ' enawon pen munkɨ pe e'nɨ'nokon. 
\c 5  
\s1 Apiyo' Pe Pʉra E'nɨto' Kʉrai Yau 
\p  
\v 1 Apiyo' pe pʉra e'nɨto' pe Kʉrai uya mo'kan nɨsa' serɨ. Mɨrɨ pɨ', pana' pe e'soto'katɨ', ke'wari'sa'tɨka'tʉu kanan apiyo' pe e'nɨto' ya' te'mʉkanse. 
\p  
\v 2 Umaimu a'si'tɨ'. Urɨ, Paarʉ uya apana'tɨ kon, ɨyun kon pi'pɨ puturʉka auya'nokon pe iyesi yau, Kʉrai esi mɨrɨ ɨnʉ' pe pʉra rɨ ɨpona'nokon.  
\v 3 Ekamakapʉ uya kanan, tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' tʉyun kon pi'pɨ puturʉkanin nan pɨ', to' tʉrawasooi pe kuru iyesi tanporon main awɨrɨ to' e'to' pe iyesi.  
\v 4 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon ekonekapaino kon main winɨ enasa' mɨrɨ ene pe Kʉrai piyapai; auta'mo'kasa' kon wakʉ nonkasa' ɨpona'nokon piyapai.  
\v 5 E'tane apurɨto' winɨ ina enurikʉ kuru serɨ Iya'kwarʉ poro ipokena' pe e'nɨto' epoto' pɨ' te'ku'to' kon pɨ'.  
\v 6 Apʉne pʉra Kʉrai Sises yau iputurʉka mɨrɨ pe pʉra iputurʉka pʉra rɨ e'nɨ esi mɨrɨ notʉn pe rɨ. Tikin nan nɨken ti'tusen esi apurɨto', tiwano' pe tʉusenpoikasen usi'nʉnkan nɨto' poro. 
\p  
\v 7 Wakʉ kuru rɨ eka'tun nɨto' yau ɨyeka'tumʉ kon esi'pʉ. Ɨnʉ' uya ken ɨyereutanʉkʉ'pʉ kon mɨrɨ i'nairon apurɨto' auya'nokon piyapai?  
\v 8 Mɨrɨ waraino iku'to' pe pori'manin uyepʉ pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ kʉrɨ ɨkɨ'manin kon nʉ'pʉ winɨ.  
\v 9 “Aiko rʉ'kwɨ rɨ pʉrowa a'sarutanʉ'nin e'tʉrawasoma mɨrɨ tanporon iki'masa' yau.”\x - \xo 5:9 \xt 1 Koren 5:6\x* 
\v 10 Uyenu yau rɨ e'ai', Itepuru yau, tʉron nɨ pe ene auya'nokon pen nɨ tukai'. Kʉrɨ ɨyeno'ma kon pɨ' na'ne' a'pai kon utaka'mato' ya' uya rɨ itepe'pʉ pe e'ma mɨrɨ, ɨnʉ' pe rɨ ken nai.  
\v 11 Utonpa ton, iputurʉka pɨ' rɨ marɨ usaurokʉ yau, ɨ'rɨ pe ken iyesi pɨ' ɨsɨ pe rɨ to' uya ukupʉ rɨ marɨ? Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ' si, kurusu' uya ɨkɨnʉntanʉ'nɨto' useno'ma'pʉ.  
\v 12 Kamoro si usauro'nɨ pɨ' te'san asakoropanin kon esi i'se e'ai' miyarɨ rɨ tʉ'ma'kai' akʉ'pɨtʉ pɨ'! 
\p  
\v 13 Ɨmɨrɨ'nokon, utonpa ton kɨ'masa' a'sisa' pe ɨwesi kon pa pen, e'tane a'sisa' pe pʉra ɨwe'to' kon ɨku'tɨ' nin ɨri eseru\f + \fr 5:13 \fq ɨri eseru; \ft mɨrɨ pe pʉra, \fq pun; \ft v. 16-17, 19, 24 nɨrɨ.\f* kupʉ pɨ'; e'tane ru'ku, ɨsiyapiyo' pe e'tɨ' ɨusi'nʉnkato' kon yau.  
\v 14 Tanporo main amʉrasa' mɨrɨ tikin nan nɨ main ya': “Ɨtonpa i'nʉnkakɨ ɨmɨrɨ pe mɨsi'nʉnkayai'ne' kasa rɨ,”\f + \fr 5:14 \ft Ripaiti'kas 19:18\f* tukai'.  
\v 15 Usi'kapɨ' nɨ pɨ' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ utan nɨ pɨ' ɨwesi kon yau, ɨsiwano' pe rɨ auma'ta kon mɨrɨ. 
\s1 Uko'man Nɨto' Ita'kwarʉ Winɨ 
\p  
\v 16 Mɨrɨ pɨ' si ta uya, ɨko'mantɨ' Ita'kwarʉ winɨ, mɨrɨ a'tai i'naino ɨri eseru pori'ma auya'nokon pʉra iyesi mɨrɨ.  
\v 17 Apʉne pʉra i'naino esi Ita'kwarʉ kaisaron pe pʉra rɨ, mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ Ita'kwarʉ esi i'naino kaisaron pe pʉra rɨ nɨrɨ. Tʉusewa'nomasan pe rɨ to' esi; i'se ɨwe'to' kon kupʉ auya'nokon poken pʉra rɨ.\x - \xo 5:17 \xt Ron 7:15-23\x* 
\v 18 E'tane Ita'kwarʉ esi pe iyesi yau ayanin kon pe, main o'no ɨwesi kon pen mɨrɨ. 
\p  
\v 19 I'naino makoi tʉrawasooi esi tense rɨ: ekuman nɨto', ɨri eseru kupʉ pɨ' e'nɨto', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ unɨkɨrun nɨto',  
\v 20 papa tato' pe ipɨ' ika'sa' pɨ' ɨpʉreman nɨto', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ enwoke' pe e'nɨto'; ɨsewaruma'ke' pe e'nɨto', ɨsipɨ' e'nɨto', ɨkɨntan nɨto', ipan pe rɨ usakorotan nɨto', amʉre' pe e'nɨto', ɨseseru yau pʉra e'nɨto', eseru wannɨ pɨkɨrɨ usewa'noman nɨto',  
\v 21 mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ikinike' pe e'nɨto'; e'taripan nɨto', te'kamai' rɨ e'taripan ekuman nɨto' pe, mɨrɨ ton warai'nan. Apanamakapʉ uya 'nokon serɨ, wapiya siku'taine' kasa, kamoro serɨ kasa tʉuko'mansan uya Papa e'to' esa' wannɨ pe anʉnto' oton pen nɨ. 
\p  
\v 22 E'tane Ita'kwarʉ eperu ton esi usi'nʉnkan nɨto', pori' pe e'nɨto', tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto', tʉuseta'kai' pʉra e'nɨto', mannʉ' pe e'nɨto', wakʉ pe e'nɨto', main nʉ'pʉ awɨrɨ e'nɨto',  
\v 23 ɨsɨ pe pʉra e'nɨto', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ iwano' wannɨ pe tʉuse'se'tɨi' e'nɨto'. Serɨ ton namai'no main pʉra rɨ iyesi mɨrɨ.  
\v 24 Kamoro Kʉrai Sises iwano' pe te'san uya kurusu' pona ti'naino kon ɨri eseru, ɨri pe e'pai te'to' kon mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ekumapai te'to' kon pokapɨtʉ'pʉ kurusu' pona.  
\v 25 Ita'kwarʉ winɨ uko'man nɨ'nokon pɨ', Ita'kwarʉ pɨkɨrɨ e'nɨpai'nokon.  
\v 26 Mɨ pe te'ku'sen pe enanpai'nokon pʉra, tonpa tʉsakoropai' pʉra, tɨkɨntai' pʉra e'nɨpai'nokon. 
\c 6  
\s1 Wakʉ Kupʉ Tanporon Kon Pɨ' 
\p  
\v 1 Utonpa ton, ɨnʉ' rɨ e'makoimasa' a'tai, ɨmɨrɨ'nokon, ta'kwarʉ ke na'ne' nan nʉna'poi ɨ'sɨ'mʉn yai. E'tane ɨsenkɨ, a'tai pʉra ɨi'tupɨ'to' rɨ marɨ esi.  
\v 2 Ɨtonpa kon wari'sarʉ atɨ'; mɨrɨ a'tai, Kʉrai maimu a'ku'tɨ auya'nokon mɨrɨ.  
\v 3 Ɨnʉ' rɨ usenuminka pe iyesi yau ɨnʉ' pe tesi tukai', ɨnʉ' pe pʉra rɨ esii'ma, tiwano' pe rɨ isenku'tɨ mɨrɨ.  
\v 4 Tɨwɨ ka'pon teseru i'tui. Mɨrɨ tʉpo, mɨ pe te'ku'to' pe, tʉron nɨ pokon pe tʉusi'tui' pʉra,  
\v 5 apʉne pʉra tʉkaisarɨ'nokon tʉwari'sarʉ kon arɨ to' uya mɨrɨ. 
\p  
\v 6 Ɨnʉ' rɨ tenupato' anʉnnin main yau esi a'tai, tɨwɨ tanporo wakʉ ton pe te'sen ekamʉi tenupanin ena'. 
\p  
\v 7 Kɨsenku'tɨtʉu: Papa esi ɨnʉ' nʉsapemanʉ pen nɨ. Ka'pon uya tʉnpɨmɨ'pʉ rɨ anʉmʉ mɨrɨ.  
\v 8 Kʉrɨ rɨ ti'naino ku'nin tʉpori'manin pe esi a'tai, mɨrɨ i'naino uya ima'tanʉkʉ; kʉrɨ rɨ wakʉ Iya'kwarʉ pori'manin pe ipɨnnin esi a'tai, Iya'kwarʉ winɨpai inkero' uko'man nɨto' eporo iya.  
\v 9 Useta'kanpai'nokon pʉra man wakʉ eseru ku'tane, apʉne pʉra itepe'pʉ anʉnto' oton kon iweyu a'tai, useta'kan nɨsa' pʉra iyesi yau.  
\v 10 Mɨrɨ pe iyesi pɨ', uweyu kon esi koro'tau, wakʉ eseru ku'pai'nokon tanporon kon ka'pon amʉ' pɨ', kamoro kuru Papa Maimu apurɨnin nan pe te'san pɨ'. 
\s1 Iputurʉka Pen E'tane Emenna' Pe E'ka'nɨ 
\p  
\v 11 Eke ton imenu entɨ' ɨyena'nokon imenuka uya koro'tau uyemiyatʉ ke! 
\p  
\v 12 Kamoro atapurɨpaino kon kɨpo'pon pɨ' rɨ aya'kwarʉka i'se na'ne' nan ɨyun kon pi'pɨ puturʉkapɨtʉ pɨ'. Tʉkota'ma kon namai' rɨken to' uya ikupʉ Kʉrai kurusukuui wenai.  
\v 13 Kamoro nin iputurʉkapɨ'sa' na'ne' nan esi main awɨrɨ pʉra rɨ. Tʉutapurɨto' kon pe ɨputurʉkapɨtʉ i'se 'nokon to' esi.  
\v 14 Atapurɨpai pʉra e'ai' e'tane uyepuru kon Sises Kʉrai kurusukuui pɨ' rɨken utapurɨ, iporo upona orʉ e'pokapɨtʉ'pʉ na'ne', mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ urɨ rɨ e'pokapɨtʉ'pʉ na'ne' ipona.  
\v 15 Iputurʉkato' mɨrɨ pe pʉra iputurʉkato' pen esi ɨ'rɨ pe pʉra rɨ; emenna' pe nin e'ka'nɨto' usi'tu mɨrɨ.  
\v 16 Tʉusewankamai' pʉra e'nɨto' mɨrɨ awonsi'kɨ ɨsentu'ke' pe e'nɨto' esi tanporo serɨ iporo e'nɨto' iyawɨrɨ te'san pona kan pe, kamo rɨ nɨrɨ Papa iwano' ton nɨrɨ Esuwerʉ amʉ' pona. 
\p  
\v 17 Iu'matʉ pe, ɨnʉ' uya rɨ uyanpokʉma i'se pʉra e'ai', apʉne pʉra Sises wenai ukota'ma'pʉ ɨ rʉ'pʉ man upɨ'. 
\p  
\v 18 Sises Kʉrai, uyepuru kon uya wakʉ nonkasa' nesii aya'kwarʉ kon piyau, utonpa ton. Amen.